In league of it's own. Just Marvelous and Superlative stuff. Very pinkish touch of Blues and western accent to Punjabi followed by Nabeel Shaukat Ali's Track with Punjabi lyrics and Sindhi tune. Sounds like Sindh Meets Punjab.

I never thought i would Listen to this kind of rendition of Umraan Langiyaan, Amazing rendition I must say. A Tribute to Asad Amanat Ali was surely a long long time Coming.. Coke Studio did it.

snippet.textDisplay: Gorgeous duet! Ali Sethi and Nabeel Shaukat Ali shared great synchrony with their goosebump-inducing vocals. A new Coke Studio 8 favourite for me! Not that I'm complaining, but given that both love songs seem to be from a female perspective I wonder if Coke Studio considered two female vocalists instead? Perhaps Fariha Pervez and Zara Madani could have done justice to this too?
